{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":360,"text":"It's a pleasure to be here"},{"time":1779,"text":"in Edinburgh, Scotland,"},{"time":3728,"text":"the birthplace of the needle and syringe."},{"time":6891,"text":"Less than a mile from here in this direction,"},{"time":9732,"text":"in 1853 a Scotsman"},{"time":11706,"text":"filed his very first patent on the needle and syringe."},{"time":14134,"text":"His name was Alexander Wood,"},{"time":16236,"text":"and it was at the Royal College of Physicians."},{"time":19987,"text":"This is the patent."},{"time":22465,"text":"What blows my mind when I look at it even today"},{"time":25176,"text":"is that it looks almost identical"},{"time":27349,"text":"to the needle in use today."},{"time":29106,"text":"Yet, it's 160 years old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32666,"text":"So we turn to the field of vaccines."},{"time":35161,"text":"Most vaccines are delivered with"},{"time":37390,"text":"the needle and syringe, \nthis 160-year-old technology."},{"time":41534,"text":"And credit where it's due -- on many levels,"},{"time":43445,"text":"vaccines are a successful technology."},{"time":47096,"text":"After clean water and sanitation,"},{"time":50985,"text":"vaccines are the one technology that has increased"},{"time":55259,"text":"our life span the most."},{"time":57789,"text":"That's a pretty hard act to beat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60264,"text":"But just like any other technology,"},{"time":62057,"text":"vaccines have their shortcomings,"},{"time":63902,"text":"and the needle and syringe"},{"time":66538,"text":"is a key part within that narrative --"},{"time":68741,"text":"this old technology."},{"time":71670,"text":"So let's start with the obvious:"},{"time":73969,"text":"Many of us don't like the needle and syringe."},{"time":77451,"text":"I share that view."},{"time":79365,"text":"However, 20 percent of the population"},{"time":82557,"text":"have a thing called needle phobia."},{"time":84833,"text":"That's more than disliking the needle;"},{"time":86594,"text":"that is actively avoiding being vaccinated"},{"time":89063,"text":"because of needle phobia."},{"time":90927,"text":"And that's problematic in terms \nof the rollout of vaccines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94934,"text":"Now, related to this is another key issue,"},{"time":97079,"text":"which is needlestick injuries."},{"time":99412,"text":"And the WHO has figures"},{"time":101384,"text":"that suggest about 1.3 million deaths per year"},{"time":105219,"text":"take place due to cross-contamination"},{"time":107611,"text":"with needlestick injuries."},{"time":108895,"text":"These are early deaths that take place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111577,"text":"Now, these are two things that \nyou probably may have heard of,"},{"time":114558,"text":"but there are two other shortcomings"},{"time":116438,"text":"of the needle and syringe you \nmay not have heard about."},{"time":118922,"text":"One is it could be holding back"},{"time":120903,"text":"the next generation of vaccines"},{"time":122382,"text":"in terms of their immune responses."},{"time":124671,"text":"And the second is that it could be responsible"},{"time":127598,"text":"for the problem of the cold chain\nthat I'll tell you about as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132210,"text":"I'm going to tell you about some work"},{"time":133792,"text":"that my team and I are doing in Australia"},{"time":135860,"text":"at the University of Queensland"},{"time":137601,"text":"on a technology designed to \ntackle those four problems."},{"time":141998,"text":"And that technology is called the Nanopatch."},{"time":146343,"text":"Now, this is a specimen of the Nanopatch."},{"time":152817,"text":"To the naked eye"},{"time":154466,"text":"it just looks like a square"},{"time":156650,"text":"smaller than a postage stamp,"},{"time":159549,"text":"but under a microscope"},{"time":162215,"text":"what you see are thousands of tiny projections"},{"time":164533,"text":"that are invisible to the human eye."},{"time":166754,"text":"And there's about 4,000 projections"},{"time":168511,"text":"on this particular square compared to the needle."},{"time":171907,"text":"And I've designed those projections"},{"time":174551,"text":"to serve a key role, which is to \nwork with the skin's immune system."},{"time":178601,"text":"So that's a very important function"},{"time":180996,"text":"tied in with the Nanopatch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182452,"text":"Now we make the Nanopatch"},{"time":184699,"text":"with a technique"},{"time":187236,"text":"called deep reactive ion etching."},{"time":189615,"text":"And this particular technique \nis one that's been borrowed"},{"time":191659,"text":"from the semiconductor industry,"},{"time":193286,"text":"and therefore is low cost"},{"time":195122,"text":"and can be rolled out in large numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197316,"text":"Now we dry-coat vaccines to \nthe projections of the Nanopatch"},{"time":202382,"text":"and apply it to the skin."},{"time":204201,"text":"Now, the simplest form of application"},{"time":208757,"text":"is using our finger,"},{"time":210779,"text":"but our finger has some limitations,"},{"time":213399,"text":"so we've devised an applicator."},{"time":215483,"text":"And it's a very simple device --"},{"time":216970,"text":"you could call it a sophisticated finger."},{"time":219088,"text":"It's a spring-operated device."},{"time":222128,"text":"What we do is when we apply \nthe Nanopatch to the skin as so --"},{"time":225950,"text":"(Click) --"},{"time":227819,"text":"immediately a few things happen."},{"time":230736,"text":"So firstly, the projections on the Nanopatch"},{"time":234783,"text":"breach through the tough outer layer"},{"time":236460,"text":"and the vaccine is very quickly released --"},{"time":238506,"text":"within less than a minute, in fact."},{"time":240854,"text":"Then we can take the Nanopatch off"},{"time":243420,"text":"and discard it."},{"time":245358,"text":"And indeed we can make \na reuse of the applicator itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251244,"text":"So that gives you an idea of the Nanopatch,"},{"time":253980,"text":"and immediately you can see some key advantages."},{"time":256556,"text":"We've talked about it being needle-free --"},{"time":258496,"text":"these are projections that you can't even see --"},{"time":260730,"text":"and, of course, we get around"},{"time":262441,"text":"the needle phobia issue as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265514,"text":"Now, if we take a step back and think about"},{"time":267445,"text":"these other two really important advantages:"},{"time":270841,"text":"One is improved immune \nresponses through delivery,"},{"time":274877,"text":"and the second is getting rid of the cold chain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278471,"text":"So let's start with the first one, \nthis immunogenicity idea."},{"time":280843,"text":"It takes a little while to get our heads around,"},{"time":282849,"text":"but I'll try to explain it in simple terms."},{"time":286578,"text":"So I'll take a step back and explain to you"},{"time":288428,"text":"how vaccines work in a simple way."},{"time":291838,"text":"So vaccines work by introducing into our body"},{"time":294415,"text":"a thing called an antigen"},{"time":296518,"text":"which is a safe form of a germ."},{"time":299695,"text":"Now that safe germ, that antigen,"},{"time":301715,"text":"tricks our body into mounting an immune response,"},{"time":305220,"text":"learning and remembering \nhow to deal with intruders."},{"time":309288,"text":"When the real intruder comes along"},{"time":311656,"text":"the body quickly mounts an immune response"},{"time":313417,"text":"to deal with that vaccine"},{"time":315053,"text":"and neutralizes the infection."},{"time":316953,"text":"So it does that well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318643,"text":"Now, the way it's done today \nwith the needle and syringe,"},{"time":320980,"text":"most vaccines are delivered that way --"},{"time":323431,"text":"with this old technology and the needle."},{"time":325115,"text":"But it could be argued that the needle \nis holding back our immune responses;"},{"time":330264,"text":"it's missing our immune sweet spot in the skin."},{"time":333706,"text":"To describe this idea,"},{"time":336702,"text":"we need to take a journey through the skin,"},{"time":339191,"text":"starting with one of those projections"},{"time":341815,"text":"and applying the Nanopatch to the skin."},{"time":344260,"text":"And we see this kind of data."},{"time":346660,"text":"Now, this is real data --"},{"time":348469,"text":"that thing that we can see there is one projection"},{"time":350815,"text":"from the Nanopatch that's been applied to the skin"},{"time":353271,"text":"and those colors are different layers."},{"time":355196,"text":"Now, to give you an idea of scale,"},{"time":356480,"text":"if the needle was shown here, it would be too big."},{"time":358420,"text":"It would be 10 times bigger"},{"time":359945,"text":"than the size of that screen,\ngoing 10 times deeper as well."},{"time":362867,"text":"It's off the grid entirely."},{"time":365082,"text":"You can see immediately that we \nhave those projections in the skin."},{"time":368275,"text":"That red layer is a tough outer layer of dead skin,"},{"time":371327,"text":"but the brown layer and the magenta layer"},{"time":373841,"text":"are jammed full of immune cells."},{"time":377022,"text":"As one example, in the brown layer"},{"time":378878,"text":"there's a certain type of cell \ncalled a Langerhans cell --"},{"time":381232,"text":"every square millimeter of our body"},{"time":383445,"text":"is jammed full of those Langerhans cells,"},{"time":386465,"text":"those immune cells, and \nthere's others shown as well"},{"time":388568,"text":"that we haven't stained in this image."},{"time":390363,"text":"But you can immediately see that the Nanopatch"},{"time":392543,"text":"achieves that penetration indeed."},{"time":394280,"text":"We target thousands upon thousands \nof these particular cells"},{"time":397709,"text":"just residing within a hair's width"},{"time":400047,"text":"of the surface of the skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403328,"text":"Now, as the guy that's invented\nthis thing and designed it to do that,"},{"time":407090,"text":"I found that exciting. But so what?"},{"time":410526,"text":"So what if you've targeted cells?"},{"time":412478,"text":"In the world of vaccines, what does that mean?"},{"time":415281,"text":"The world of vaccines is getting better."},{"time":417702,"text":"It's getting more systematic."},{"time":419426,"text":"However, you still don't really know"},{"time":421648,"text":"if a vaccine is going to work"},{"time":423392,"text":"until you roll your sleeves up"},{"time":424731,"text":"and vaccinate and wait."},{"time":426946,"text":"It's a gambler's game even today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429648,"text":"So, we had to do that gamble."},{"time":432160,"text":"We obtained an influenza vaccine,"},{"time":434640,"text":"we applied it to our Nanopatches"},{"time":436256,"text":"and we applied the Nanopatches to the skin,"},{"time":438727,"text":"and we waited --"},{"time":440460,"text":"and this is in the live animal."},{"time":442288,"text":"We waited a month,"},{"time":444139,"text":"and this is what we found out."},{"time":445951,"text":"This is a data slide showing the immune responses"},{"time":448276,"text":"that we've generated with a Nanopatch"},{"time":450599,"text":"compared to the needle and syringe into muscle."},{"time":454375,"text":"So on the horizontal axis we have \nthe dose shown in nanograms."},{"time":457969,"text":"On the vertical axis we have \nthe immune response generated,"},{"time":460674,"text":"and that dashed line indicates \nthe protection threshold."},{"time":466189,"text":"If we're above that line it's considered protective;"},{"time":468642,"text":"if we're below that line it's not."},{"time":471568,"text":"So the red line is mostly below that curve"},{"time":474136,"text":"and indeed there's only one point that \nis achieved with the needle that's protective,"},{"time":477660,"text":"and that's with a high dose of 6,000 nanograms."},{"time":480869,"text":"But notice immediately the distinctly different curve"},{"time":483402,"text":"that we achieve with the blue line."},{"time":486466,"text":"That's what's achieved with the Nanopatch;"},{"time":488366,"text":"the delivered dose of the Nanopatch is"},{"time":490103,"text":"a completely different immunogenicity curve."},{"time":493464,"text":"That's a real fresh opportunity."},{"time":495297,"text":"Suddenly we have a brand new lever"},{"time":497675,"text":"in the world of vaccines."},{"time":499203,"text":"We can push it one way,"},{"time":500714,"text":"where we can take a vaccine \nthat works but is too expensive"},{"time":503305,"text":"and can get protection"},{"time":504964,"text":"with a hundredth of the dose \ncompared to the needle."},{"time":507788,"text":"That can take a vaccine that's suddenly \n10 dollars down to 10 cents,"},{"time":511839,"text":"and that's particularly important \nwithin the developing world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515019,"text":"But there's another angle to this as well --"},{"time":516886,"text":"you can take vaccines that currently don't work"},{"time":519938,"text":"and get them over that line"},{"time":521134,"text":"and get them protective."},{"time":523092,"text":"And certainly in the world of vaccines"},{"time":525320,"text":"that can be important."},{"time":526540,"text":"Let's consider the big three:"},{"time":528038,"text":"HIV, malaria, tuberculosis."},{"time":530735,"text":"They're responsible for about \n7 million deaths per year,"},{"time":533327,"text":"and there is no adequate vaccination \nmethod for any of those."},{"time":536534,"text":"So potentially, with this new lever \nthat we have with the Nanopatch,"},{"time":539066,"text":"we can help make that happen."},{"time":540901,"text":"We can push that lever to help get those \ncandidate vaccines over the line."},{"time":545771,"text":"Now, of course, we've worked within my lab"},{"time":547589,"text":"with many other vaccines that have attained"},{"time":549379,"text":"similar responses and similar curves to this,"},{"time":552197,"text":"what we've achieved with influenza."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555962,"text":"I'd like to now switch to talk about"},{"time":558121,"text":"another key shortcoming of today's vaccines,"},{"time":561453,"text":"and that is the need to maintain the cold chain."},{"time":564873,"text":"As the name suggests -- the cold chain --"},{"time":567547,"text":"it's the requirements of keeping \na vaccine right from production"},{"time":570487,"text":"all the way through to when the vaccine is applied,"},{"time":573163,"text":"to keep it refrigerated."},{"time":576261,"text":"Now, that presents some logistical challenges"},{"time":579507,"text":"but we have ways to do it."},{"time":582497,"text":"This is a slightly extreme case in point"},{"time":587033,"text":"but it helps illustrate the logistical challenges,"},{"time":589516,"text":"in particular in resource-poor settings,"},{"time":591906,"text":"of what's required to get vaccines"},{"time":595192,"text":"refrigerated and maintain the cold chain."},{"time":596910,"text":"If the vaccine is too warm the vaccine breaks down,"},{"time":600724,"text":"but interestingly it can be too cold"},{"time":602931,"text":"and the vaccine can break down as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605492,"text":"Now, the stakes are very high."},{"time":608874,"text":"The WHO estimates that within Africa,"},{"time":611409,"text":"up to half the vaccines used there"},{"time":614060,"text":"are considered to not be working properly"},{"time":615913,"text":"because at some point the \ncold chain has fallen over."},{"time":618903,"text":"So it's a big problem, and it's tied \nin with the needle and syringe"},{"time":621469,"text":"because it's a liquid form vaccine, and \nwhen it's liquid it needs the refrigeration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626702,"text":"A key attribute of our Nanopatch"},{"time":629213,"text":"is that the vaccine is dry,"},{"time":631186,"text":"and when it's dry it doesn't need refrigeration."},{"time":633975,"text":"Within my lab we've shown that we can keep"},{"time":636387,"text":"the vaccine stored at 23 degrees Celsius"},{"time":639067,"text":"for more than a year without \nany loss in activity at all."},{"time":642783,"text":"That's an important improvement."},{"time":645170,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":651770,"text":"We're delighted about it as well."},{"time":654233,"text":"And the thing about it is that\nwe have well and truly proven"},{"time":658529,"text":"the Nanopatch within the laboratory setting."},{"time":661192,"text":"And as a scientist, I love that and I love science."},{"time":665165,"text":"However, as an engineer,"},{"time":667673,"text":"as a biomedical engineer"},{"time":669386,"text":"and also as a human being,"},{"time":671589,"text":"I'm not going to be satisfied"},{"time":672820,"text":"until we've rolled this thing \nout, taken it out of the lab"},{"time":675513,"text":"and got it to people in large numbers"},{"time":677944,"text":"and particularly the people that need it the most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681480,"text":"So we've commenced this particular journey,"},{"time":684182,"text":"and we've commenced this \njourney in an unusual way."},{"time":686843,"text":"We've started with Papua New Guinea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689832,"text":"Now, Papua New Guinea is an example \nof a developing world country."},{"time":695637,"text":"It's about the same size as France,"},{"time":698773,"text":"but it suffers from many of the key barriers"},{"time":701608,"text":"existing within the world of today's vaccines."},{"time":705676,"text":"There's the logistics:"},{"time":707289,"text":"Within this country there are only 800 \nrefrigerators to keep vaccines chilled."},{"time":711647,"text":"Many of them are old, like this one in Port Moresby,\nmany of them are breaking down"},{"time":715940,"text":"and many are not in the Highlands \nwhere they are required."},{"time":718856,"text":"That's a challenge."},{"time":720319,"text":"But also, Papua New Guinea has the \nworld's highest incidence of HPV,"},{"time":725502,"text":"human papillomavirus, the \ncervical cancer [risk factor]."},{"time":729733,"text":"Yet, that vaccine is not available in large numbers"},{"time":732434,"text":"because it's too expensive."},{"time":734348,"text":"So for those two reasons, with \nthe attributes of the Nanopatch,"},{"time":737094,"text":"we've got into the field and \nworked with the Nanopatch,"},{"time":739709,"text":"and taken it to Papua New Guinea"},{"time":742160,"text":"and we'll be following that up shortly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746143,"text":"Now, doing this kind of work is not easy."},{"time":749625,"text":"It's challenging,"},{"time":750973,"text":"but there's nothing else in \nthe world I'd rather be doing."},{"time":754297,"text":"And as we look ahead"},{"time":756320,"text":"I'd like to share with you a thought:"},{"time":760062,"text":"It's the thought of a future where"},{"time":764070,"text":"the 17 million deaths per year"},{"time":766003,"text":"that we currently have due to infectious disease"},{"time":768347,"text":"is a historical footnote."},{"time":770981,"text":"And it's a historical footnote that has been achieved"},{"time":773077,"text":"by improved, radically improved vaccines."},{"time":776545,"text":"Now standing here today in front of you"},{"time":778828,"text":"at the birthplace of the needle and syringe,"},{"time":780501,"text":"a device that's 160 years old,"},{"time":783298,"text":"I'm presenting to you an alternative approach"},{"time":785634,"text":"that could really help make that happen --"},{"time":787883,"text":"and it's the Nanopatch with its attributes \nof being needle-free, pain-free,"},{"time":791865,"text":"the ability for removing the cold chain\nand improving the immunogenicity."},{"time":796296,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":798249,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}